1. Create a vpc with 4 subnets two public and two private
   a. use vpc and more ( name the vpc abc )

2. ec2 
   a. create a sg called abc-ec2-sg
   b. allow http and ssh from every where and allow all outbound traffic
   c. create two ec2 in abc vpc, one in us-east-1a public subnet
      one in us-east-1b public subnet, allow auto assign public Ip
   d. use this user data
      #!/bin/bash
      dnf install httpd php php-mysqlnd -y 
      systemctl start httpd
      echo hello $(hostname) > /var/www/html/index.html
   e. access the public ip of your instances and make sure that they are working fine

3. target group
  a. create a target group called abc-tg
  b. port 80 
  c. use abc vpc 
  d. add the EC2s created instances to the target group

4. loadbalancer
  a. create a security group called alb-sg in abc vpc, allow http from every where and allow all outbound traffic
  b. use public subnets in the abc vpc
  c. add listener port 80, target group alb-tg
  d. wait until the alb is active, test it's dns name in your browser and make sure that it's working fine
  e. working fine ? if yes, update the abc-ec2-sg to allow only http from the alb-sg

5. RDS
  a. create a security group called rds-sg allow only mysql(3306) trafffic from the abc-ec2-sg
  and create a subnet group called private-subnet-group ( add only private subnets to it )
  b. create rds instance with free tier template in us-east-1a az of abc vpc ( choose the subnet group created earlier )
  c. choose a username and password
  d. edit the index.php file with the correct username,password, host
  e. replace the index.html with index.php and test

  
